  "additional_info": "Tested working with Firefox 9.x (with and without Stylish) and Chromium 16.something (without Stylish) on Ubuntu 10.10 Maverick. (<strong>Update:</strong> Re-tested with Firefox Nightly 28.0a1 and Chromium 30.0.1599.114 both using the latest Stylish extension on Ubuntu 12.04.) A happy Valentine's Day gift to the Simplenote users who have been <a href=\"http://help.simplenoteapp.com/customer/portal/questions/57081-mono-spaced-font\">requesting this feature</a> for a while.\r\n\r\nThe Simplenote web app's borders in the screenshot have been removed by <a href=\"http://userstyles.org/styles/40848/simplenote-remove-border\">this userstyle</a>. Also seen in this screenshot: the Resurrect Pages, Pinboard.in, and Omnibar Firefox extensions, plus the DuckDuckGo search plugin. <strong>Update 2013-11-23: still works after Automattic acquisition and iOS 7-ish redesign.</strong>  \r\n\r\nIf this style helps you out and you feel like <strong>externalizing your joy by giving away some money</strong>, please consider <a href=\"https://donate.mozilla.org/\">donating to the Mozilla Foundation</a>, the creators of the Firefox web browser, without which I couldn't have created this style. (Okay, <a href=\"http://getfirebug.com/contribute\">Firebug</a> and <a href=\"https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/stylish\">Stylish</a> helped, too.)",
  "style_tags": [],
  "css": "@namespace url(http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml);\r\n\r\n@-moz-document domain(\"simple-note.appspot.com\") {\r\n    div.note textarea#txtarea {\r\n        font-family: /*[[fontfamily]]*/ !important;\r\n        font-size: /*[[fontsize]]*/ !important;\r\n    }\r\n}",
